# Cursor AI News — Project Root (NOT PasteCraft)

When the user talks about **Cursor AI News**, all work belongs in **CursorAINews**, not PasteCraft.

## Canonical project root

**Absolute path:** `C:\Dev\CursorAINews`

| What | Path |
|---|---|
| Project root | `C:\Dev\CursorAINews` |
| App (Expo + API) | `C:\Dev\CursorAINews\mobile` |
| API server | `C:\Dev\CursorAINews\mobile\server` |
| Web preview (optional) | `C:\Dev\CursorAINews\web` |
| Docs (canonical) | `C:\Dev\CursorAINews\docs` |
| Server onboarding (local) | `mobile/server/AGENT-CONTEXT.md` |

## Mandatory agent behavior

1. **Scope all reads, edits, terminals, and commits** to `C:\Dev\CursorAINews` and its subdirectories.
2. When workspace is **`mobile/server`**, read **`AGENT-CONTEXT.md`** in this folder first.
3. For phased feed-service work, follow **`unofficial-cursor-news-feed-service.mdc`** (repo `.cursor/rules/` or this folder).

## Explicit forbiddens

| Wrong (PasteCraft) | Right (CursorAINews) |
|---|---|
| `C:\Dev\PasteCraft\` for news feed code | `mobile/`, `mobile/server/`, `web/` |
| PasteCraft `extension/` | `mobile/server/src/`, `mobile/src/` |

## Product identity

- **Cursor AI News / Unofficial Cursor News** — unofficial fan app; not affiliated with Anysphere.
- **PasteCraft** — separate browser-extension product.
